body:
+1 
@ernisv Could you squash commits into one? 
Btw, I feel this patch should be along with STORM-2296, so if we would want to port this back to 1.0.x, STORM-2296 should be ported back first.

@ernisv 
Could you change your commit title to be meaningful? We often set commit title to same as JIRA title.
I can take care of other things so you don't need to worry about that.

@srdo the changes proposed in this PR handle null tuples in identical fashion that what is done in the old KafkaSpout, as can be seen in the following links. Namely, the old Spout behavior is to silently ack discard null tuples. Here we are logging that we may be directly acking a null tuple, such that it's not completely silent.

https://github.com/apache/storm/blob/master/external/storm-kafka/src/jvm/org/apache/storm/kafka/PartitionManager.java#L197

https://github.com/apache/storm/blob/master/external/storm-kafka/src/jvm/org/apache/storm/kafka/PartitionManager.java#L208-L210
